      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "An ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "NSScriptExecutionContext",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " object is a shared instance (there is only one instance of the class) that represents the context in which the current script command is executed. ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "NSScriptExecutionContext",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " tracks global state relating to the command being executed, especially the top-level container object (that is, the container implied by a specifier object that specifies no container) used in an evaluation of an ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsscriptobjectspecifier",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " object.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "In most cases, the top-level container for a complete series of nested object specifiers is automatically set to the application object (",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "NSApp",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": "), and you can get this object with the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsscriptexecutioncontext/1415288-toplevelobject",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " method. But you can also set this top-level container to something else (using ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsscriptexecutioncontext/1415288-toplevelobject",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ") if the situation warrants it.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "It is unlikely that you will need to subclass ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "NSScriptExecutionContext",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
